CNCP v1 23392
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#9943: Component name not inferred when using `<component :is=\"...\"`  for recursive use",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:23:16.070851+00:00",
  "text": "Component name not inferred when using `<component :is=\"...\"`  for recursive use\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.4.0\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://stackblitz.com/edit/vitejs-vite-dt2kjn?file=src%2Fcomponents%2FComp2.vue\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create component that would have `<component :is=\"getComponentName()\"> ` in template. From STR - Comp2.vue\r\n2. Implement `getComponentName` in a way, so it would conditionally resolve to a component name from step (1). In my sample - I just tried to render same component inside several times\r\n3. Observe that `<comp2 depth=\"1\"></comp2>` is generated in DOM \r\n4. Set  `name`  to `Comp2` for a component.\r\n5. Observe that component renders to certain depth as expected\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nComp2 component name to be inferred as documented in https://vuejs.org/api/options-misc.html#name\r\n\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nComp2 component name not inferred and setting component name explicitly is required\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\nIn my other tests I found out that component name is inferred as expected if I explicitly use `<Comp2>`  in its own template, so issue is only with a scenario when name is dynamically computed.\r\nhttps://stackblitz.com/edit/vitejs-vite-xucve7?file=src%2Fcomponents%2FComp2.vue",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "has workaround",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
